  "sam_altman_chunk_6": [
    "OpenAI\nOpenAI begins\nOpenAI was initially founded as a nonprofit organization by Altman, Greg Brockman, Elon Musk, Jessica Livingston, Peter Thiel, Microsoft, Amazon Web Services, Infosys, and YC Research. Altman tenaciously recruited Ilya Sutskever and Dario Amodei by giving them attention and offering YC stock. In his early conversations with Musk, he framed OpenAI as competing against Google's AI development. Google was far ahead; Musk and Altman modeled their strategy after the Manhattan Project with an emphasis on recruiting AI technology leaders and convincing the world that they were protecting against the AI threat.\nWhen OpenAI launched in 2015, it had raised pledges for $1 billion. In 2019, OpenAI said that $130 million of the pledged funds had been collected. TechCrunch reported that YC Research never contributed any of their pledged funds.\nAltman said in 2015 that they were partly motivated by concerns about AI safety and existential risk from artificial general intelligence. Altman highlighted the importance of open-source and making AI for collective good for humanity, above financial stakeholders in response to mitigation of risk. Altman noted it will be a decades-long project that eventually surpasses human intelligence. Walter Isaacson opined that Altman had \"Musk-like intensity\"."
  ]
}

